Note:
Runa Emitter - Buffered output for Runa canonical-syntax code generation

All buffer management, character/string emission, and indentation logic
is delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa.

Conventions:
- 4-space indentation for Runa canonical syntax
- Null-terminated output strings
:End Note

Import "../emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

@Reasoning:
Typed handle distinguishing Runa source emission from foreign-language
backends in the dispatch table. Used by the round-trip path
(HIR -> Runa canonical) for formatter/printer infrastructure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three fields shadow the raw EmitterCommon byte buffer (pointer, capacity,
length). All actual storage lives in the shared arena.
@End Implementation

Type called "RunaEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Factory that keeps EmitterCommon as a private dependency of this file.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_runa_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric lifecycle pair for create_runa_emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee the handle was produced by create_runa_emitter and
has not already been destroyed; double-free is the caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_runa_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pre-sizing hook so callers that know they are about to emit a large
module can avoid repeated realloc churn.
@End Reasoning

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-byte emission for punctuation, operators, and quote delimiters.
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(1) amortized.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bulk emission for Runa keywords, identifiers, and pre-formatted fragments.
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(n) in input length.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Convenience for the common pattern of emitting a Runa statement followed
by a newline.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then appends ASCII LF (10). Project convention is LF
line endings on all platforms.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Standalone newline used when terminating a block header or inserting a
blank separator between top-level forms.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Spaces are emitted between every Runa token pair where canonical syntax
requires whitespace.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Runa canonical syntax uses 4-space indentation per the project style
guide; the emitter materializes that directly instead of relying on a
post-pass formatter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Unrolled inner loop emits four ASCII SPACE bytes per indent level,
avoiding the multiply-then-loop pattern used by other emitters because
the constant 4 is fixed for Runa output.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(level) bytes. Called once per emitted statement.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: 4-space indentation for Runa canonical syntax.
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than level:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated Runa source so the driver can hand it to disk
or to the parser for round-trip verification.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Returned pointer aliases the emitter's internal buffer. Caller must not
free it directly and must not use it after destroy_runa_emitter.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes current byte count for golden-output diff tools.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lets the driver reuse a single emitter across multiple translation units
without paying allocation cost for each one.
@End Reasoning

Process called "reset" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
